00:16:09,160 --> 00:16:11,870
The one who Denkyu saw was not an illusion.

261
00:16:11,870 --> 00:16:13,170
No.

262
00:16:13,170 --> 00:16:15,570
The one who was wearing the earring

263
00:16:15,570 --> 00:16:17,070
was probably either Bunkyu or Rinkyu

264
00:16:17,070 --> 00:16:22,140
who were disciples here at this temple until two months ago.

265
00:16:22,140 --> 00:16:24,050
Bunkyu and Rinkyu?

266
00:16:24,050 --> 00:16:26,550
Remember, I mentioned a while ago that

267
00:16:26,550 --> 00:16:30,450
I adopted two other children besides Denkyu.

268
00:16:30,450 --> 00:16:34,960
Unlike Denkyu, they were both forever prone to mischief.

269
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:38,860
They used to sneak out of the temple night after night and go to town.

270
00:16:38,860 --> 00:16:40,060
Moreover, they used to disguise themselves as women

271
00:16:40,060 --> 00:16:42,560
so people wouldn't suspect them to be monks.

272
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:43,970
Disguise?

273
00:16:43,970 --> 00:16:47,170
Yes. I don't know where they got a hold of it

274
00:16:47,170 --> 00:16:50,070
but they wore a wig, pierced earrings and a long dress,

275
00:16:50,070 --> 00:16:53,580
just like those the young people wear nowadays.

276
00:16:53,580 --> 00:16:55,180
Is that true?

277
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:56,750
Yes.

278
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:58,550
Those two used to frequently drink liquor

279
00:16:58,550 --> 00:17:01,050
secretly in this annex too.

280
00:17:01,050 --> 00:17:04,250
Osho found out about it, and the two had a good scolding.

281
00:17:04,250 --> 00:17:09,260
They didn't like it, so they both left this temple together.

282
00:17:09,260 --> 00:17:13,660
They seem to have been using this annex to change clothes and all,

283
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:16,870
so the backing must've accidentally come off.

284
00:17:16,870 --> 00:17:19,770
So, that's the story! Convinced?

285
00:17:21,870 --> 00:17:24,870
You still don't look convinced, I see.

286
00:17:24,870 --> 00:17:28,380
Then do check things out for yourselves to your heart's content.

287
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:29,650
If as Denkyu says

288
00:17:29,650 --> 00:17:33,150
there was a blood smeared corpse in the middle of the room,

289
00:17:33,150 --> 00:17:37,750
the blood should be found somewhere on the tatami.

290
00:17:39,250 --> 00:17:41,260
Ran.

291
00:17:41,260 --> 00:17:42,960
Don't you think Heiji and the others are a bit late?

292
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:46,560
Yeah, I wonder if something happened.

293
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:50,070
Okay, Ran, wait here then! I'll go check!

294
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:52,270
Oh, I'll go too, then!

295
00:18:00,780 --> 00:18:02,440
Don't you think that it's better for us

296
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:06,450
to just wait here without moving after all, Ran?

297
00:18:06,650 --> 00:18:08,650
I guess so.

298
00:18:30,170 --> 00:18:34,180
Around where on the floor was that woman?

299
00:18:34,380 --> 00:18:37,550
Oh, yes. She was right around here three days ago,

300
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:40,350
lying on the floor like this.

301
00:18:40,350 --> 00:18:43,550
Then, what about the woman you saw a while ago?

302
00:18:43,550 --> 00:18:45,650
In the middle of the room,

303
00:18:45,650 --> 00:18:47,160
like so.

304
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:49,560
Was there a lot of blood?

305
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:50,860
Yeah.

306
00:18:50,860 --> 00:18:52,760
Three days ago as well as tonight,

307
00:18:52,760 --> 00:18:55,560
there was a lot of bleeding from the stomach.

308
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:59,170
Then, 10 to 1 it's not possible.

309
00:18:59,170 --> 00:19:01,670
Maybe possible with the corpse he saw yesterday.

310
00:19:01,670 --> 00:19:06,070
But if the corpse he saw lying there just a while ago is real,

311
00:19:06,070 --> 00:19:09,950
there should be a blood stained tatami on the side

312
00:19:09,950 --> 00:19:13,950
but even looks around now, there's no such tatami around!

313
00:19:14,050 --> 00:19:16,450
You think so too. Did I actually see

314
00:19:16,450 --> 00:19:20,860
an illusion of my mother that never existed in the first place after all?

315
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:25,060
So, are you convinced now?

316
00:19:25,060 --> 00:19:26,960
Yes, very.

317
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:30,170
Then, Denkyu, please show these people to the gate.

318
00:19:30,170 --> 00:19:31,170
Yes, sir.

319
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:34,170
I'll stay here in this room for a while

320
00:19:34,170 --> 00:19:36,070
and offer prayer to the Four Heavenly Kings

321
00:19:36,070 --> 00:19:40,080
in apology of having been a bit of a nuisance with all the fuss here.

322
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:45,750
I'm sorry for keeping you here for so long because of my mistake.

323
00:19:45,750 --> 00:19:50,250
No, don't be, but why were you there at that time in that annex?

324
00:19:50,250 --> 00:19:52,050
I always go and check to see

325
00:19:52,050 --> 00:19:54,760
if the doors are locked before dinner.

326
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:57,860
Bunkyu and Rinkyu

327
00:19:57,860 --> 00:20:02,970
were actually in charge of cleaning and locking the annex up.

328
00:20:02,970 --> 00:20:04,770
But, after their drinking incident,

329
00:20:04,770 --> 00:20:09,070
Osho did the cleaning and I was in charge of locking up.

330
00:20:09,070 --> 00:20:11,070
Not only did they drink liquor,

331
00:20:11,070 --> 00:20:13,880
but I'll be the two were also smoking in there too?

332
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:15,840
How do you know?

333
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:20,450
They both said they succeeded in smoking secretly.

334
00:20:20,450 --> 00:20:22,050
What a conspicuous secret.

335
00:20:22,050 --> 00:20:25,650
There was an obviously burnt spot on the tatami.

336
00:20:25,650 --> 00:20:28,760
Come to think of it, there were remains of spilt beer too.

337
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:32,760
Yeah but what I don't understand is why both the remains...

338
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:36,470
They weren't there when we checked at sundown today.

339
00:20:36,470 --> 00:20:38,470
Right, Heiji?

340
00:20:38,470 --> 00:20:40,370
-Right! -Don't tell me that

341
00:20:40,370 --> 00:20:43,470
someone switched the tatami?

342
00:20:43,470 --> 00:20:46,070
I'm just saying that it's possible.

343
00:20:46,070 --> 00:20:47,680
No way.

344
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:50,250
I'm sure you guys already know if you checked too,

345
00:20:50,250 --> 00:20:53,950
but the tatami at the annex was not double-sided,

346
00:20:53,950 --> 00:20:57,950
and besides, it was old and discolored from the sun.

347
00:20:57,950 --> 00:20:59,350
Even if a tatami from someplace else

348
00:20:59,350 --> 00:21:01,160
were to have been brought in and replaced,

349
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:03,760
the discoloration would make it apparent.

350
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:06,760
You mean switching isn't possible?

351
00:21:06,760 --> 00:21:10,770
Switching the tatami of one of the four 8-mat floors.

352
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:12,670
To go from Pop's car to that annex

353
00:21:12,670 --> 00:21:15,170
would take 7 to 8 minutes going and coming back,

354
00:21:15,170 --> 00:21:18,170
if you run, that's enough time to switch the tatami!

355
00:21:18,170 --> 00:21:21,080
Come to think of it, something always felt different from usual,

356
00:21:21,080 --> 00:21:22,840
each time I found the bodies.

357
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:24,350
Right? I'll bet

358
00:21:24,350 --> 00:21:26,650
the direction the tatami is placed or something is different?

359
00:21:26,650 --> 00:21:29,550
Oh, but it's only that I have this feeling.

360
00:21:29,550 --> 00:21:31,950
No matter how you replace the tatami,

361
00:21:31,950 --> 00:21:33,260
you can't hide the blood stain.

362
00:21:33,260 --> 00:21:36,160
If the body was lying smeared with blood in the middle of the room,

363
00:21:36,160 --> 00:21:40,760
there should be blood on more than two tatamis!

364
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:42,060
Well, the only thing that did look suspicious

365
00:21:42,060 --> 00:21:45,970
were the statues of the Four Heavenly Kings in the corner of the rooms

366
00:21:45,970 --> 00:21:48,570
but they were inside transparent glass cases.

367
00:21:48,570 --> 00:21:52,370
When the statue was moved, the tatami under it was in view,

368
00:21:52,370 --> 00:21:54,680
so the blood couldn't have been hidden.

369
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:56,750
Let's pull out, pull out!

370
00:21:56,750 --> 00:22:00,250
I can't be wasting my time on this silly story!

371
00:22:02,550 --> 00:22:04,950
Huh? A mistake?

372
00:22:04,950 --> 00:22:07,960
Are you saying that there was no corpse?

373
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:10,760
No, it was this monk's illusion.

374
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:12,060
I'm sorry.

375
00:22:12,060 --> 00:22:15,460
But, I'm glad that nobody was dead then.

376
00:22:15,460 --> 00:22:18,570
Okay, hurry and get in then, so we can head back to Ran's house.

377
00:22:19,570 --> 00:22:20,670
The pinwheel.

378
00:22:20,670 --> 00:22:22,470
Oh no, I squashed it.

379
00:22:22,470 --> 00:22:25,170
It's okay, because it's not all that bent out of shape.

380
00:22:25,170 --> 00:22:26,580
Why?

381
00:22:26,580 --> 00:22:29,240
Why did the burnt remain that wasn't there at sundown

382
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:32,050
appear suddenly at night?

383
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:34,050
It was hidden out of sight?

384
00:22:34,050 --> 00:22:35,750
But, where?

385
00:22:39,250 --> 00:22:41,060
Heiji...

386
00:22:45,760 --> 00:22:48,160
Hey, you...

387
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:54,870
This is it! This!

388
00:22:54,870 --> 00:22:57,470
I've figured out where the blood stain is hidden!

389
00:22:57,470 --> 00:22:59,680
Yeah, I thought of that too!

390
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:01,480
Yeah,

391
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,450
completely!

392
00:23:11,110 --> 00:23:13,020
"Orange. Pinwheel Room" -I've figured it out completely!

393
00:23:13,270 --> 00:23:15,170
"Orange. Pinwheel Room" -You meant that the woman

394
00:23:15,170 --> 00:23:17,440
that I saw three days ago and the one I saw tonight were...

395
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:20,840
Yeah, not an illusion but genuine dead bodies

396
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:24,140
that were ingeniously hidden and made to look as if they disappeared

397
00:23:24,140 --> 00:23:26,550
using an unimaginable trick.

398
00:23:26,550 --> 00:23:27,750
Trick?

399
00:23:27,750 --> 00:23:30,050
What kind of trick was it?

400
00:23:30,050 --> 00:23:31,750
Please tell us, dad!

401
00:23:32,550 --> 00:23:36,860
The hint is this pinwheel! This brought everything to light!

402
00:23:36,860 --> 00:23:38,860
You thought so too, didn't you?

403
00:23:38,860 --> 00:23:40,460
Osaka kid.

404
00:23:40,460 --> 00:23:42,960
Yeah.

405
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:44,160
Why did the corpse disappear

406
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:47,870
when Denkyu took us to the annex with him and returned?

407
00:23:47,870 --> 00:23:50,640
Let's say that this pinwheel is the annex.

408
00:23:50,640 --> 00:23:52,340
There is no railing at the annex

409
00:23:52,340 --> 00:23:54,940
and there are four square 8-mat rooms.

410
00:23:56,340 --> 00:23:57,740
Railing?

411
00:23:57,740 --> 00:23:59,150
Square?

412
00:23:59,150 --> 00:24:02,050
Oh my, you mean the third-rate detective kid of Osaka

413
00:24:02,050 --> 00:24:04,450
can't figure it out yet?

414
00:24:04,450 --> 00:24:06,850
No, I can't make out your deduction.

415
00:24:06,850 --> 00:24:12,360
Yes. It rotated 180 degrees, that annex!

416
00:24:15,260 --> 00:24:18,970
I don't think there's such a contraption in that annex.

417
00:24:18,970 --> 00:24:20,770
You just don't know of it.

418
00:24:20,770 --> 00:24:23,640
I hear that the annex was built 50 years ago.

419
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:25,140
Even so,

420
00:24:25,140 --> 00:24:28,240
three days ago the police, and tonight you people,

421
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:29,940
who were called by me, after coming here

422
00:24:29,940 --> 00:24:33,950
investigated every nook and cranny, of all four rooms, didn't you?

423
00:24:33,950 --> 00:24:34,950
Back then,

424
00:24:34,950 --> 00:24:38,350
no blood nor corpse was found in any of the rooms, right?

425
00:24:38,350 --> 00:24:40,150
Yeah, that's right.

426
00:24:40,150 --> 00:24:41,550
Besides,

427
00:24:41,550 --> 00:24:45,160
if such an amusement park like building existed 50 years ago,

428
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:50,760
it would've become a famous site around here. Dumb-dumb!

429
00:24:50,760 --> 00:24:52,370
Then...

430
00:24:52,370 --> 00:24:57,040
There was no dead body so it was just your illusion!

431
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:59,940
No, there was blood as well as the corpse.

432
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:04,740
Although they were hidden and out of sight.

433
00:25:04,740 --> 00:25:08,250
Hidden... where on earth?

434
00:25:08,250 --> 00:25:09,350
Ouch.

435
00:25:09,350 --> 00:25:11,050
Conan!

436
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:15,560
Are you all right?

437
00:25:15,560 --> 00:25:18,960
I slipped when I tried to pick up the badge I dropped.

438
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:20,860
You've gotta be careful.

439
00:25:20,860 --> 00:25:23,060
It seems to be quite muddy around here yet

440
00:25:23,060 --> 00:25:24,960
from the rain this morning.

441
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:26,870
By the way, do you see my detective badge

442
00:25:26,870 --> 00:25:29,440
somewhere around here?

443
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:31,040
No, I don't see it.

444
00:25:31,040 --> 00:25:33,940
Here's your glasses.

445
00:25:33,940 --> 00:25:35,540
Thank you!

446
00:25:35,540 --> 00:25:37,140
There's your badge.

447
00:25:37,140 --> 00:25:38,240
Oh, yeah.

448
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:42,050
But, how strange... it wasn't there a while ago.

449
00:25:42,050 --> 00:25:43,450
That's true.

450
00:25:43,450 --> 00:25:47,450
Maybe it's because of the leaf that's stuck on this glasses.

451
00:25:47,650 --> 00:25:51,160
See, you can see the badge if it's like this

452
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:53,860
but, if you put the glasses with the leaf on it like this,

453
00:25:53,860 --> 00:25:56,960
you can't see it anymore.

454
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:59,970
Really. It's mixed up with the leaves on the ground.

455
00:25:59,970 --> 00:26:02,440
And it looks like there's no badge there.

456
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:07,640
Hey, maybe the same sort of trick was used?

457
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:08,840
Could be.

458
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:10,640
A trick?

459
00:26:10,640 --> 00:26:13,350
Yeah, if this trick is used,

460
00:26:13,350 --> 00:26:15,450
maybe even blood can be hidden.

461
00:26:15,450 --> 00:26:17,850
Under the case of the statues of the Four Heavenly Kings

462
00:26:17,850 --> 00:26:20,750
that were in the corner of the rooms of the annex.

463
00:26:20,750 --> 00:26:23,560
There was nothing below the cases.

464
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:25,560
The tatami below was in view under the case

465
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:27,260
when I moved the statue too.

466
00:26:27,260 --> 00:26:29,460
So if you cut the tatami

467
00:26:29,460 --> 00:26:31,460
and paste the front side of the tatami onto the back of the glass case

468
00:26:31,460 --> 00:26:35,070
and if it were placed on top of the tatami where the blood stain is...

469
00:26:35,070 --> 00:26:37,440
The blood would be completely covered

470
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:38,940
and it would look as if you're looking at the tatami below

471
00:26:38,940 --> 00:26:40,940
through the glass case, wouldn't it?

472
00:26:40,940 --> 00:26:42,540
True.

473
00:26:42,540 --> 00:26:45,650
But, the trick would give itself away

474
00:26:45,650 --> 00:26:47,450
as soon as somebody lifts the case up, right?

475
00:26:47,450 --> 00:26:48,950
No way.

476
00:26:48,950 --> 00:26:51,850
If you lift the glass case with the statue inside it,

477
00:26:51,850 --> 00:26:55,860
it may fall and crack the glass,

478
00:26:55,860 --> 00:26:57,060
besides if you move the statue that's inside,

479
00:26:57,060 --> 00:26:59,960
it looks as if the tatami below is in view through the glass.

480
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:01,460
Nobody would think of going out of the way

481
00:27:01,460 --> 00:27:03,460
to move the case after doing so!

482
00:27:03,460 --> 00:27:06,770
I didn't move the case myself either.

483
00:27:06,770 --> 00:27:11,640
But, who for what reason would've set up a trick like that?

484
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:16,540
Would the killer do something like that to hide the blood?

485
00:27:16,540 --> 00:27:18,850
The ones who set up this trick

486
00:27:18,850 --> 00:27:22,350
were probably the two monks who left this temple two months ago,

487
00:27:22,350 --> 00:27:23,850
in order to hide the liquor stains

488
00:27:23,850 --> 00:27:25,550
and burnt remains from their cigarettes.

489
00:27:25,550 --> 00:27:27,450
They probably went out to look for tatami

490
00:27:27,450 --> 00:27:29,960
that was very close in color to the one in the annex

491
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:33,460
and pasted it on to the bottom of the glass case of the statue,

492
00:27:33,460 --> 00:27:37,160
to hide the stain and remains of burns.

493
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:40,970
Those two were in charge of cleaning the annex,

494
00:27:40,970 --> 00:27:43,140
and besides they told you that they succeeded

495
00:27:43,140 --> 00:27:44,740
in pulling the trick, right?

496
00:27:44,740 --> 00:27:46,240
Yes.

497
00:27:46,240 --> 00:27:48,140
When we checked the annex at sundown,

498
00:27:48,140 --> 00:27:50,440
we found nothing like that and yet,

499
00:27:50,440 --> 00:27:52,350
when you came and told us you found the corpse

500
00:27:52,350 --> 00:27:54,350
and we went to check,

501
00:27:54,350 --> 00:27:56,950
it suddenly appeared, that's the proof.

502
00:27:56,950 --> 00:27:58,250
Then, you mean

503
00:27:58,250 --> 00:28:01,450
the two monks who left snuck back in here

504
00:28:01,450 --> 00:28:04,860
and killed a woman from somewhere?

505
00:28:04,860 --> 00:28:08,360
No. The two just set up the trick.

506
00:28:08,360 --> 00:28:09,960
The one who used it

507
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:11,360
is the one who saw through their trick

508
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:14,170
and bawled the two out.

509
00:28:14,970 --> 00:28:16,340
That is, no one else could've done it

510
00:28:16,340 --> 00:28:18,640
besides head monk Shakuren, right?

511
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:20,340
You mean that Osho did it?

512
00:28:20,340 --> 00:28:23,240
You mean he killed the woman?

513
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:24,640
No.

514
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:27,950
If he killed somebody, he wouldn't have returned to the temple

515
00:28:27,950 --> 00:28:29,450
and sleep like nothing happened

516
00:28:29,450 --> 00:28:32,050
till Denkyu found the corpse three days ago.

517
00:28:32,050 --> 00:28:34,650
That woman most probably committed suicide.

518
00:28:34,650 --> 00:28:38,460
Osho, who heard from Denkyu that a woman was dead in the annex,

519
00:28:38,460 --> 00:28:40,960
probably came up with the idea on the spur of the moment.

520
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:42,960
He decided to say that it was Denkyu's illusion

521
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:46,170
