00:41:22,580 --> 00:41:25,680
please stay in your rooms and don't leave until dinner time.

778
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:29,590
So, if anything's going to happen, it will be after dinner.

779
00:41:29,590 --> 00:41:31,090
But be on your guard,

780
00:41:31,090 --> 00:41:32,690
because the match is already started

781
00:41:32,690 --> 00:41:35,590
as soon as you step foot on the island.

782
00:41:35,590 --> 00:41:36,900
Okay.

783
00:41:36,900 --> 00:41:39,200
Roger.

784
00:41:39,200 --> 00:41:41,700
Strange, I figured everyone would be more excited

785
00:41:41,700 --> 00:41:45,500
because this is a Detective Championship Game.

786
00:41:45,500 --> 00:41:48,810
And why did you bring me along?

787
00:41:48,810 --> 00:41:50,110
Don't tell me that you want me to team with you

788
00:41:50,110 --> 00:41:51,880
so that you can win or something?

789
00:41:51,880 --> 00:41:56,380
No, Shinichi Kudo of the east can't come anyway.

790
00:41:56,380 --> 00:41:59,480
That's why I figured you should come and join us too.

791
00:41:59,480 --> 00:42:02,990
It'll be too boring if I win the game just like that.

792
00:42:02,990 --> 00:42:05,890
You're about the only one here that's an equal match for me.

793
00:42:05,890 --> 00:42:09,890
But, you even brought Ran and the others over too.

794
00:42:09,990 --> 00:42:14,400
I wouldn't come to such a corny game alone myself either.

795
00:42:20,810 --> 00:42:23,510
Are you seasick?

796
00:42:23,510 --> 00:42:26,380
Oh, no. It's a hang-over.

797
00:42:26,380 --> 00:42:28,280
It took a while to shoot yesterday so...

798
00:42:28,280 --> 00:42:31,480
I went out drinking with the staff after we finished, and got wasted.

799
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:36,390
So, you went "overboard".

800
00:42:36,390 --> 00:42:37,790
"Overboard?"

801
00:42:37,790 --> 00:42:42,190
Well, the shop was really high priced.

802
00:42:42,190 --> 00:42:46,100
Hey, mister, this is in the way, laugh, will you? It's too narrow.

803
00:42:46,100 --> 00:42:48,700
Laugh? A narrow heart.

804
00:42:48,700 --> 00:42:52,500
Oh, you were playing on words using "overboard" and "high."

805
00:42:54,710 --> 00:42:59,280
Those two seem pretty sharp.

806
00:42:59,280 --> 00:43:01,380
Detective Championship Game?

807
00:43:01,380 --> 00:43:03,180
Nichuri TV?

808
00:43:03,180 --> 00:43:07,090
We have no such reservation.

809
00:43:07,090 --> 00:43:09,490
Hey, check it out carefully, will you?

810
00:43:09,490 --> 00:43:12,290
Dinner and breakfast are supposed to be included too.

811
00:43:12,290 --> 00:43:14,990
-Yes, but... -What?

812
00:43:14,990 --> 00:43:16,790
What's going on?

813
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:26,200
Welcome.

814
00:43:26,200 --> 00:43:28,610
I'm the one who will be taking care of you,

815
00:43:28,610 --> 00:43:30,210
my name is Renzo Koya.

816
00:43:30,210 --> 00:43:34,080
Nice to meet you all. I'll show you to your lodge.

817
00:43:34,080 --> 00:43:36,480
Hey, director.

818
00:43:36,480 --> 00:43:39,880
If the high school detective of the east isn't coming,

819
00:43:39,880 --> 00:43:43,290
I'd like to talk something over with you.

820
00:43:43,290 --> 00:43:45,290
Huh?

821
00:43:45,290 --> 00:43:47,190
The representative from the east

822
00:43:47,190 --> 00:43:50,700
arrived here early this morning and is already at the lodge.

823
00:43:50,700 --> 00:43:53,500
What did you say? Is that true?

824
00:43:53,500 --> 00:43:56,500
If I remember correctly, his name was...

825
00:44:02,510 --> 00:44:04,210
I see.

826
00:44:04,210 --> 00:44:05,180
"Please cancel tomorrow's" -This is indeed

827
00:44:05,180 --> 00:44:06,380
"Please cancel tomorrow's" -an isolated island cut off

828
00:44:06,380 --> 00:44:08,980
"dinner reservation." -from the outside world.

829
00:44:08,980 --> 00:44:14,390
There couldn't be a situation better than this for a mystery.

830
00:44:15,790 --> 00:44:17,790
Saguru Hakuba?

831
00:44:19,890 --> 00:44:22,190
Who is he?

832
00:44:27,760 --> 00:44:28,760
"White. Highschool Detective in East" -So, now

833
00:44:28,760 --> 00:44:30,370
"White. Highschool Detective in East" -since the high school detectives

834
00:44:30,370 --> 00:44:32,170
of the east, west, south and north are all here

835
00:44:32,170 --> 00:44:34,070
let's start with self-introduction!

836
00:44:34,070 --> 00:44:35,370
Okay.

837
00:44:35,370 --> 00:44:38,070
Are you're sure you don't mind the cameras not rolling?

838
00:44:38,070 --> 00:44:41,740
I mean, there are no TV staff here at all!

839
00:44:41,740 --> 00:44:44,250
Oh, the crew and TV talent who is MC for this program

840
00:44:44,250 --> 00:44:46,150
are scheduled to be arriving tomorrow.

841
00:44:46,150 --> 00:44:49,850
I wanted all of you to be here a day ahead.

842
00:44:49,850 --> 00:44:51,250
Okay then.

843
00:44:51,250 --> 00:44:54,360
I'm Natsuki Koshimizu, a junior in high school.

844
00:44:54,360 --> 00:44:58,260
I was born in Fukuoka and is representing the south.

845
00:44:58,260 --> 00:45:00,960
But, I've only solved about 100 cases to date,

846
00:45:00,960 --> 00:45:02,660
so am still a beginner,

847
00:45:02,660 --> 00:45:04,370
so take it easy on me, okay?

848
00:45:04,370 --> 00:45:06,770
My name is Junya Tokitsu.

849
00:45:06,770 --> 00:45:09,570
I was born in Tokyo, but since I was raised in Hokkaido,

850
00:45:09,570 --> 00:45:12,070
I'm here representing the north.

851
00:45:12,070 --> 00:45:14,340
I've solved up to 300 cases up to date.

852
00:45:14,340 --> 00:45:17,650
People have been arrested and indicted in 250 of those cases.

853
00:45:17,650 --> 00:45:19,450
But there were people who escaped

854
00:45:19,450 --> 00:45:22,450
or committed suicide among them too.

855
00:45:22,450 --> 00:45:23,850
I'm Heiji Hattori.

856
00:45:23,850 --> 00:45:26,960
I'm pretty well-known in the Kansai district.

857
00:45:26,960 --> 00:45:31,260
The number of cases that I've solved so far is one, two, three...

858
00:45:31,260 --> 00:45:33,860
Well, with over a thousand cases to my name,

859
00:45:33,860 --> 00:45:36,160
I've lost track already!

860
00:45:36,160 --> 00:45:38,370
A thousand cases.

861
00:45:38,370 --> 00:45:39,570
Wow.

862
00:45:39,570 --> 00:45:42,970
Hey, stop bluffing like that.

863
00:45:42,970 --> 00:45:44,270
It's true,

864
00:45:44,270 --> 00:45:47,040
if I include the times I searched for cats in my childhood.

865
00:45:47,040 --> 00:45:50,750
I see, so you're Heiji Hattori.

866
00:45:50,750 --> 00:45:52,950
My dad used to talk a lot about you.

867
00:45:52,950 --> 00:45:55,250
He said that you're a detective with very keen intuition.

868
00:45:55,250 --> 00:45:57,250
Huh?

869
00:45:57,250 --> 00:45:59,850
How come your dad knows me?

870
00:45:59,850 --> 00:46:01,960
Because he's the same as you, Heiji.

871
00:46:01,960 --> 00:46:02,960
Same as me?

872
00:46:02,960 --> 00:46:04,960
Right, Hakuba?

873
00:46:04,960 --> 00:46:08,060
Yeah, my father is a police commissioner.

874
00:46:08,060 --> 00:46:09,260
So, strangely enough,

875
00:46:09,260 --> 00:46:11,570
I lived in an environment similar to yours being that

876
00:46:11,570 --> 00:46:15,070
your father was the leader of the Osaka Prefectural Police.

877
00:46:15,070 --> 00:46:18,170
By the way, how many cases have you solved?

878
00:46:18,170 --> 00:46:21,540
Well, I guess just about 500 cases.

879
00:46:21,540 --> 00:46:23,540
What? That's only half the number compared to mine!

880
00:46:23,540 --> 00:46:26,750
Yes, but that's if I limit the cases

881
00:46:26,750 --> 00:46:29,150
to those that I solved here in Japan.

882
00:46:29,150 --> 00:46:30,550
What?

883
00:46:30,550 --> 00:46:33,050
I've been staying in England as an exchange student for awhile

884
00:46:33,050 --> 00:46:35,860
and only returned to Japan occasionally,

885
00:46:35,860 --> 00:46:37,260
but my nanny would take on requests

886
00:46:37,260 --> 00:46:39,760
for solving cases of her own discretion.

887
00:46:39,760 --> 00:46:41,560
It's so unexpected that

888
00:46:41,560 --> 00:46:44,870
Hakuba who is famous abroad is here representing the east.

889
00:46:44,870 --> 00:46:48,670
Yep, I was so sure that it was going to be Shinichi Kudo.

890
00:46:48,670 --> 00:46:51,470
Right, the high school detective of the east

891
00:46:51,470 --> 00:46:55,940
is none other than Shinichi Kudo, right? It's not you!

892
00:46:55,940 --> 00:47:00,650
My nanny took the call from the director over there.

893
00:47:00,650 --> 00:47:03,150
He said that he wanted me to participate in place of Shinichi Kudo

894
00:47:03,150 --> 00:47:06,750
who he couldn't get a hold of as representative of the east.

895
00:47:06,750 --> 00:47:10,260
Nanny was hurt by the phrase, "in place of"

896
00:47:10,260 --> 00:47:12,260
and pleaded in tears for me to show the world

897
00:47:12,260 --> 00:47:16,060
that Hakuba is the high school detective of the east.

898
00:47:17,270 --> 00:47:20,370
So, I had no choice but to come back from England.

899
00:47:20,370 --> 00:47:22,070
That's the story,

900
00:47:22,070 --> 00:47:25,670
but it seems that I'm not suited to represent the east, am I?

901
00:47:25,670 --> 00:47:27,340
Of course you're not.

902
00:47:27,340 --> 00:47:28,940
Then, why don't we do this?

903
00:47:28,940 --> 00:47:32,950
I'm a guest participant from abroad.

904
00:47:33,150 --> 00:47:37,150
We'll appoint Conan Edogawa here as representative of the east.

905
00:47:37,150 --> 00:47:40,350
This young man here is pretty good at deductions too.

906
00:47:40,350 --> 00:47:42,060
I'm sure he is equal to if not better than the youth called...

907
00:47:42,060 --> 00:47:43,660
what's his name, Kudo.

908
00:47:43,660 --> 00:47:46,460
"What's his name"?

909
00:47:46,460 --> 00:47:48,160
But he's still a child...

910
00:47:48,160 --> 00:47:50,670
Who cares, no problem.

911
00:47:50,670 --> 00:47:52,470
I'd like to go to my room quickly.

912
00:47:52,470 --> 00:47:53,670
I'm pooped.

913
00:47:53,670 --> 00:47:55,870
I'd like to have dinner too.

914
00:47:55,870 --> 00:47:57,970
Oh, right.

915
00:47:57,970 --> 00:48:01,340
Okay. Mr. Koya is making dinner now

916
00:48:01,340 --> 00:48:03,850
so I'll come get all of you when it's ready.

917
00:48:03,850 --> 00:48:06,650
Oh, and I'd like to check your outfits that you'll be wearing

918
00:48:06,650 --> 00:48:07,850
when shooting the program tomorrow,

919
00:48:07,850 --> 00:48:09,150
so please wear it when coming to dinner.

920
00:48:09,150 --> 00:48:11,850
Make sure you wear outfits that suit the Detective Championship Game

921
00:48:11,850 --> 00:48:13,750
as we talked over the telephone.

922
00:48:13,750 --> 00:48:15,760
Huh, what?

923
00:48:15,760 --> 00:48:17,660
There's no such program?

924
00:48:17,660 --> 00:48:19,460
Is that true, Yoko?

925
00:48:19,460 --> 00:48:22,860
No, I asked around the TV station,

926
00:48:22,860 --> 00:48:24,670
but nobody's heard of a special program

927
00:48:24,670 --> 00:48:26,070
called Detective Championship Game.

928
00:48:26,070 --> 00:48:29,670
Are you sure the man was really from Nichiuri TV?

929
00:48:29,670 --> 00:48:32,370
Yeah, he was wearing the stadium jumper of the station

930
00:48:32,370 --> 00:48:36,240
and his name is Hiroo Tsuchio.

931
00:48:36,240 --> 00:48:37,250
What?

932
00:48:37,250 --> 00:48:39,850
There's no director by that name?

933
00:48:39,850 --> 00:48:44,950
-Then who was that man... -That took the two of them?

934
00:48:44,950 --> 00:48:46,150
I see,

935
00:48:46,150 --> 00:48:48,760
that's what you call an outfit suited for the Detective Championship game.

936
00:48:48,760 --> 00:48:51,260
Yeah, I hate to dress like this

937
00:48:51,260 --> 00:48:53,560
other than to school or funerals.

938
00:48:53,560 --> 00:48:58,570
But, what a surprise that you knew that snobbish guy.

939
00:48:58,570 --> 00:49:00,470
Oh, you mean Suguru Hakuba.

940
00:49:00,470 --> 00:49:02,270
I met him when solving a case in the past.

941
00:49:02,270 --> 00:49:04,470
Did he get you that upset?

942
00:49:04,470 --> 00:49:08,440
Yeah, I hate the snobbish way he talks, like he's looking down at you.

943
00:49:08,640 --> 00:49:11,350
-He so much like you. -Oh...

944
00:49:11,350 --> 00:49:15,250
Well, at least you're cute, so way better than him in a way, though.

945
00:49:15,250 --> 00:49:16,450
I see.

946
00:49:16,450 --> 00:49:20,050
But from here, we're enemies.

947
00:49:20,050 --> 00:49:24,360
Don't talk to me no matter what comes up.

948
00:49:24,360 --> 00:49:25,460
Come in?

949
00:49:25,460 --> 00:49:30,670
Excuse me. Dinner's ready, so please come to the dining room.

950
00:49:32,470 --> 00:49:35,170
This sure is an old lodge.

951
00:49:35,170 --> 00:49:37,970
It looks to be fixed here and there, though.

952
00:49:37,970 --> 00:49:39,570
Who owns this place?

953
00:49:39,570 --> 00:49:42,740
I wonder? I hear that some rich person is renting it out

954
00:49:42,740 --> 00:49:45,450
since he has no use for it anymore.

955
00:49:47,450 --> 00:49:50,850
By the way, has she already gone to the dining room?

956
00:49:50,850 --> 00:49:51,950
She?

957
00:49:51,950 --> 00:49:54,960
No, I was just about to go call her now.

958
00:49:54,960 --> 00:49:57,060
Is there a woman here on this island too?

959
00:49:57,060 --> 00:50:00,460
She was with us all the while.

960
00:50:00,460 --> 00:50:01,760
Yes!

961
00:50:03,970 --> 00:50:05,470
Dinner's ready.

962
00:50:05,470 --> 00:50:07,170
Oh, it's it time already?

963
00:50:07,170 --> 00:50:09,670
Oh no! I guess I took too much time!

964
00:50:09,670 --> 00:50:12,970
You mean, she was a woman?

965
00:50:12,970 --> 00:50:15,240
My school has strict rules.

966
00:50:15,240 --> 00:50:16,940
Skirts have to be 3 cm below the knee,

967
00:50:16,940 --> 00:50:18,450
scarves have to be symmetrical right and left,

968
00:50:18,450 --> 00:50:19,550
socks have to be black,

969
00:50:19,550 --> 00:50:21,050
and of course perms aren't allowed.

970
00:50:21,050 --> 00:50:23,050
If we shave our eyebrows, we get suspended.

971
00:50:23,050 --> 00:50:24,550
God knows how many times I was warned about

972
00:50:24,550 --> 00:50:26,150
this naturally brown hair of mine.

973
00:50:26,150 --> 00:50:28,660
But, I guess it's no big deal tonight

974
00:50:28,660 --> 00:50:30,660
because the cameras aren't here yet, right?

975
00:50:30,660 --> 00:50:32,760
Yeah, I guess so.

976
00:50:32,760 --> 00:50:35,360
Hey, you didn't change clothes.

977
00:50:35,360 --> 00:50:37,060
Yes, because unlike you people

978
00:50:37,060 --> 00:50:40,870
the school that I attend in England has no uniform.

979
00:50:41,370 --> 00:50:44,070
Wow, it looks delicious.

980
00:50:44,070 --> 00:50:46,170
Did you make all this, sir?

981
00:50:46,170 --> 00:50:49,040
-Yes. -Huh, where's the director?

982
00:50:49,040 --> 00:50:53,350
When I went to get him at his room a while ago, there was no answer,

983
00:50:53,350 --> 00:50:56,950
so I though he had already come here.

984
00:50:56,950 --> 00:50:59,950
Please show me to his room.

985
00:50:59,950 --> 00:51:01,860
Mr. Tsuchio.

986
00:51:01,860 --> 00:51:05,860
Dinner's ready. Mr. Tsuchio?

987
00:51:06,060 --> 00:51:09,160
No good, I guess he locked it so he could sleep.

988
00:51:15,070 --> 00:51:16,370
Blood.

989
00:51:17,970 --> 00:51:20,340
There's blood on the door knob.

990
00:51:20,340 --> 00:51:23,040
-Do you have a spare key? -No, there is no key to begin with,

991
00:51:23,040 --> 00:51:26,950
because like your rooms, the key can only be locked from inside.

992
00:51:26,950 --> 00:51:29,450
If the rooms are the same, there should be two windows.

993
00:51:29,450 --> 00:51:31,750
Then, let's look inside through the window.

994
00:51:33,150 --> 00:51:34,860
You...

995
00:51:40,560 --> 00:51:42,260
Mr. Tsuchio!

996
00:51:49,460 --> 00:51:51,060
"Gray. Highschool Detective in North" -Mr. Tsuchio!

997
00:51:51,060 --> 00:51:54,270
"Gray. Highschool Detective in North" -The window is locked.

998
00:51:54,270 --> 00:51:56,580
It seems the door was completely locked too.

999
00:51:56,740 --> 00:51:58,580
Then, this is a locked door murder case?

1000
00:52:00,080 --> 00:52:04,120
Yes, but obviously that's only if he's dead.

1001
00:52:07,700 --> 00:52:09,300
He's alive.

1002
00:52:09,300 --> 00:52:11,200
What happened?

1003
00:52:11,200 --> 00:52:13,100
What a relief! What happened?

1004
00:52:13,100 --> 00:52:16,910
Oh, somebody knocked on the door.

1005
00:52:18,910 --> 00:52:20,510
I answered the door. But, there was no one there.

1006
00:52:20,510 --> 00:52:22,010
When I was about to go back into the room,

1007
00:52:22,010 --> 00:52:24,910
I was suddenly drugged from behind.

1008
00:52:24,910 --> 00:52:29,290
Problem number one of the Detective Championship Game!

1009
00:52:29,290 --> 00:52:31,690
Solve this locked room mystery.

1010
00:52:31,690 --> 00:52:34,590
After solving the mystery, write it down

1011
00:52:34,590 --> 00:52:35,990
and bring it to me.

1012
00:52:35,990 --> 00:52:40,300
If your deduction is the truth, you will make it to the second level

1013
00:52:40,300 --> 00:52:44,300
and as well as allowed to leave this island.

1014
00:52:44,500 --> 00:52:47,800
Which means that the battle has already been launched!

1015
00:52:47,800 --> 00:52:51,810
Then, is there a hidden camera somewhere?

1016
00:52:51,810 --> 00:52:53,210
But, how unexpected.

1017
00:52:53,210 --> 00:52:55,810
I thought that the first level was to see through

1018
00:52:55,810 --> 00:52:58,410
the fact that this person is a fake director.

1019
00:52:58,410 --> 00:53:01,220
Just what do you think you're saying? I'm really...

1020
00:53:01,220 --> 00:53:02,690
Quit playing dumb with us.

1021
00:53:02,690 --> 00:53:07,190
Back then, when he said you went overboard,

1022
00:53:07,190 --> 00:53:09,990
he meant you had a tough time because the shooting

1023
00:53:09,990 --> 00:53:13,000
took all the way till after midnight.

1024
00:53:13,000 --> 00:53:16,500
And the remark, "laugh" that the girl made after that

1025
00:53:16,500 --> 00:53:19,800
means do something about something.

1026
00:53:19,800 --> 00:53:21,800
I mean you're no new AD and all.

1027
00:53:21,800 --> 00:53:26,210
There's no director that doesn't understand movie language like those.

1028
00:53:26,210 --> 00:53:29,210
Besides, that mark of Nichiuri TV that you have on you is strange.

1029
00:53:29,210 --> 00:53:31,610
The groove of the eye isn't right.

1030
00:53:31,610 --> 00:53:34,420
The real one grooves in the opposite direction.

1031
00:53:34,420 --> 00:53:38,790
That's why everyone figured you were a fake and tested you.

1032
00:53:38,790 --> 00:53:42,790
Well, you can explain after we make complete the first round though.

1033
00:53:42,990 --> 00:53:46,700
Sorry, but count me out.

1034
00:53:46,700 --> 00:53:49,000
I've figured out

1035
00:53:49,000 --> 00:53:51,100
this locked room trick.

1036
00:53:51,100 --> 00:53:53,900
Would you like me to show you?

1037
00:53:53,900 --> 00:53:55,600
You've already solved it.

1038
00:53:55,600 --> 00:53:58,210
Okay, show us.

1039
00:53:58,210 --> 00:53:59,810
No, you can't.

1040
00:53:59,810 --> 00:54:03,810
If you do so, the others will also figure out the trick.

1041
00:54:04,010 --> 00:54:05,510
So, please write your deduction down

1042
00:54:05,510 --> 00:54:08,020
and bring it to me like I mentioned a while ago.

1043
00:54:08,020 --> 00:54:11,890
This is the first round, you know, and not the finals.

1044
00:54:11,890 --> 00:54:15,490
Don't worry, he wouldn't do it right before our eyes.

1045
00:54:15,490 --> 00:54:17,390
Well, as far as I'm concerned,

1046
00:54:17,390 --> 00:54:20,800
the result would be the same even if this were to be the finals, though.

1047
00:54:20,800 --> 00:54:22,900
What confidence.

1048
00:54:22,900 --> 00:54:25,400
I hope that trick isn't something that goes like,

1049
00:54:25,400 --> 00:54:29,310
Mr. Tsuchio who was tied up in the locked room,

1050
00:54:29,310 --> 00:54:32,110
after locking the door tied himself up, is it?

1051
00:54:32,110 --> 00:54:33,310
No way,

1052
00:54:33,310 --> 00:54:34,810
because if so, the representative of the west

1053
00:54:34,810 --> 00:54:37,910
who untied him would've noticed,

1054
00:54:37,910 --> 00:54:41,220
no matter how incapable a detective he is.

1055
00:54:41,220 --> 00:54:43,190
How dare you call me incapable?

1056
00:54:43,190 --> 00:54:45,190
That's true, it wasn't smart.

1057
00:54:45,190 --> 00:54:47,590
You found blood on the door knob,

1058
00:54:47,590 --> 00:54:50,290
broke the door down and entered the room.

1059
00:54:50,290 --> 00:54:51,490
In that case,

1060
00:54:51,490 --> 00:54:53,900
we should've checked things out by looking in from the window

1061
00:54:53,900 --> 00:54:55,900
and then decide whether we should break the door down

1062
00:54:55,900 --> 00:54:57,600
or crack the window and enter.

1063
00:54:57,600 --> 00:54:59,900
Because if Mr. Tsuchio was leaning against the door

1064
00:54:59,900 --> 00:55:02,000
or moreover, dead,

1065
00:55:02,000 --> 00:55:04,610
at the point that the door is kicked open, the corpse would move,

1066
00:55:04,610 --> 00:55:07,310
as well as disperse the evidence.

1067
00:55:07,310 --> 00:55:09,010
Stupid, back then...

1068
00:55:09,010 --> 00:55:10,410
Overreaching and carrying things too far

1069
00:55:10,410 --> 00:55:13,620
for wanting to make it to scene before anyone else does.

1070
00:55:13,620 --> 00:55:16,490
Aren't such people considered disqualified as detectives?

1071
00:55:16,490 --> 00:55:17,890
Watch your tongue!

1072
00:55:17,890 --> 00:55:20,190
He's not disqualified.

1073
00:55:20,190 --> 00:55:21,890
Kudo.

1074
00:55:21,890 --> 00:55:26,200
Heiji is just a bit too quick tempered.

1075
00:55:26,200 --> 00:55:27,500
Hey...

1076
00:55:27,500 --> 00:55:30,800
At any rate, I'm going back up to my room on the second floor

1077
00:55:30,800 --> 00:55:32,600
and turn my room into a locked room,

1078
00:55:32,600 --> 00:55:35,600
so wait for me while having dinner, will you?

1079
00:55:35,600 --> 00:55:37,710
It'll take me at least an hour to do so.

1080
00:55:37,710 --> 00:55:39,010
An hour?

1081
00:55:39,010 --> 00:55:42,610
I see, the time it took Mr. Koya to show us to our rooms,

1082
00:55:42,610 --> 00:55:45,010
to the time what happened at this room

1083
00:55:45,010 --> 00:55:46,820
took just about the same time.

1084
00:55:46,820 --> 00:55:49,190
The trick is an intricate one that requires that much time.

1085
00:55:49,190 --> 00:55:51,990
Well, I guess so.

1086
00:55:51,990 --> 00:55:53,690
I'd like to say this, just in case, though.

1087
00:55:53,690 --> 00:55:56,790
This trick does not call for the foolish, uncouth detective's

1088
00:55:56,790 --> 00:55:57,990
ill-mannered actions,

1089
00:55:57,990 --> 00:55:59,400
so please keep that in mind.

1090
00:55:59,400 --> 00:56:03,100
Well, I'm sure that he won't repeat the same mistake again.

1091
00:56:03,100 --> 00:56:05,600
After all, he's got his local reputation as his father's name

1092
00:56:05,600 --> 00:56:08,100
as chief of Osaka Police Department to maintain too.

1093
00:56:08,100 --> 00:56:11,510
Right, representative of the west?

1094
00:56:11,510 --> 00:56:13,210
But...

1095
00:56:13,210 --> 00:56:17,210
I like passionate detectives like you.

1096
00:56:20,620 --> 00:56:21,580
It's a ship

1097
00:56:21,580 --> 00:56:23,390
-that was anchored around here... -What's the matter, Kazuha?

1098
00:56:23,390 --> 00:56:26,890
-and took the children. -Well, I have this bad feeling.

1099
00:56:26,890 --> 00:56:28,890
The cell phone, it's still not going through?

1100
00:56:28,890 --> 00:56:30,490
-The number you have reached... -No,

1101
00:56:30,490 --> 00:56:32,090
it's still in the out of service area,

1102
00:56:32,090 --> 00:56:33,800
and just keeps repeating that message.

1103
00:56:33,800 --> 00:56:35,100
I see.

1104
00:56:35,100 --> 00:56:39,100
Hey, Ran, don't you feel something strange?

1105
00:56:39,100 --> 00:56:42,000
Like an unidentifiable eerie something

1106
00:56:42,000 --> 00:56:44,610
is closing in on Heiji and the others.

1107
00:56:44,610 --> 00:56:46,210
I think you're letting your imagination get the better of you.

1108
00:56:46,210 --> 00:56:50,910
I'm sure that Heiji is okay and that he'll come back with Conan.

1109
00:56:50,910 --> 00:56:53,020
I know, but something bothers me.

1110
00:56:53,020 --> 00:56:55,990
The face of Heiji when he was being escorted off

1111
00:56:55,990 --> 00:56:59,090
keep twirling around in my head over and over.

1112
00:56:59,090 --> 00:57:02,290
How about Conan's cell phone?

1113
00:57:02,290 --> 00:57:03,490
You still can't contact him?

1114
00:57:03,490 --> 00:57:05,900
Nope, his is no good either.

1115
00:57:05,900 --> 00:57:08,100
I wish that the representative of the east,

1116
00:57:08,100 --> 00:57:09,600
Shinichi Kudo were there together with Heiji at a time like this.

1117
00:57:09,600 --> 00:57:12,400
I would make me feel way better.

1118
00:57:12,400 --> 00:57:16,110
The number you have reached is out of service range...

1119
00:57:16,110 --> 00:57:19,010
It's the same with Shinichi's cell phone too.

1120
00:57:19,010 --> 00:57:22,310
Don't tell me that Shinichi is with them too?

1121
00:57:38,490 --> 00:57:41,890
"Purple. Scent of Lavender"

1122
00:57:43,090 --> 00:57:45,060
It's out of service range after all.

1123
00:57:45,060 --> 00:57:47,860
Well, this is an isolated island.

1124
00:57:48,860 --> 00:57:50,660
What, no joke?

1125
00:57:50,660 --> 00:57:52,170
I just went to the restroom for a while

1126
00:57:52,170 --> 00:57:54,470
and yet there almost nothing left already.

1127
00:57:54,470 --> 00:57:56,570
Hey, mister, you're eating too much.

1128
00:57:56,570 --> 00:57:59,870
I know, I was starved, you see.

1129
00:57:59,870 --> 00:58:01,370
Gosh.

1130
00:58:01,370 --> 00:58:03,780
Okay, so now that you're filled, tell us.

1131
00:58:03,780 --> 00:58:06,680
Won't you, fake TV director?

1132
00:58:06,680 --> 00:58:09,580
Tell us why you're participating as a fake TV director

1133
00:58:09,580 --> 00:58:11,480
for this Detective Championship Game.

1134
00:58:11,480 --> 00:58:13,690
If this program is to measure our capabilities,

1135
00:58:13,690 --> 00:58:15,690
what's your role?

1136
00:58:15,690 --> 00:58:17,290
No. I can't tell you that

1137
00:58:17,290 --> 00:58:19,560
because if I do, I won't get paid. I bound by contract.

1138
00:58:19,560 --> 00:58:22,460
With Nichiuri TV?

1139
00:58:22,460 --> 00:58:25,870
Then, will you answer this question?

1140
00:58:25,870 --> 00:58:29,870
I was concerned since I set foot into this lodge

1141
00:58:29,870 --> 00:58:33,070
about the fragrance of the lavender flower over there.

1142
00:58:33,070 --> 00:58:36,180
Now that you mentioned it, there is a lavender flower in our room too.

1143
00:58:36,180 --> 00:58:37,280
Yeah.

1144
00:58:37,280 --> 00:58:38,980
There's one in my room too.

1145
00:58:38,980 --> 00:58:41,480
It seems to be in every room.

1146
00:58:41,480 --> 00:58:45,390
And that toolbox that's sitting over there.

1147
00:58:45,390 --> 00:58:47,990
There's a meaning to it too, isn't there?

1148
00:58:47,990 --> 00:58:50,090
Well, I wonder.

1149
00:58:50,090 --> 00:58:53,460
It is the detective's job to figure that out.

1150
00:58:53,460 --> 00:58:55,460
That's how I see it, is it not?

1151
00:58:55,460 --> 00:58:59,470
True, but since we're separated from the outside world,

1152
00:58:59,570 --> 00:59:01,370
we don't have the means to check.

1153
00:59:01,370 --> 00:59:04,470
Homicide at Lavender Manor.

1154
00:59:07,470 --> 00:59:10,080
The only thing lavenders bring to my mind

1155
00:59:10,080 --> 00:59:14,080
is the incident that occurred in Shikoku a year ago.

1156
00:59:14,080 --> 00:59:16,280
I've heard of that case too.

1157
00:59:16,280 --> 00:59:19,890
The one who was killed was the lady of the mansion.

1158
00:59:32,970 --> 00:59:34,970
Miss!

1159
00:59:35,670 --> 00:59:37,670
"Young Lady at the Lavender Manor Commits Suicide"

1160
00:59:37,670 --> 00:59:40,270
"Motive Unknown. The Door is Locked"

1161
00:59:40,270 --> 00:59:42,080
"Possibility of Intruder"

1162
00:59:42,080 --> 00:59:46,780
But it was found six months later that she had been murdered.

1163
00:59:46,780 --> 00:59:48,480
And? The killer?

1164
00:59:48,480 --> 00:59:50,080
Committed suicide before getting caught.

1165
00:59:50,080 --> 00:59:52,190
That's what I heard.

1166
00:59:56,390 --> 00:59:57,590
What's up?

1167
00:59:57,590 --> 00:59:59,160
No, well, you see...

1168
00:59:59,160 --> 01:00:01,560
I forgot my cigarettes in my room.

1169
01:00:06,770 --> 01:00:09,570
Wow, it's really raining cats and dogs now.

1170
01:00:13,670 --> 01:00:16,080
What's the matter? You're drenched.

1171
01:00:16,080 --> 01:00:19,280
Did you go look for a cigarette vending machine outside or something?

1172
01:00:19,280 --> 01:00:21,580
Oh, no, I just went to check how things were outside.

1173
01:00:21,580 --> 01:00:25,490
By the way, don't you think he's a bit too much time?

1174
01:00:25,490 --> 01:00:28,690
Yes, it's been more than two hours since then already.

1175
01:00:28,690 --> 01:00:30,590
I'll go ask him

1176
01:00:30,590 --> 01:00:32,160
how much longer he thinks it will take him.

1177
01:00:32,160 --> 01:00:34,260
Okay, please do.

1178
01:00:34,960 --> 01:00:37,460
What? He's not in his room?

1179
01:00:37,460 --> 01:00:39,270
No, no matter how many times I knock on the door,

1180
01:00:39,270 --> 01:00:40,370
there's no answer.

1181
01:00:40,370 --> 01:00:44,270
But, the door was locked, so maybe...

1182
01:00:44,270 --> 01:00:47,370
I see, he probably completed the locked room

1183
01:00:47,370 --> 01:00:49,680
and is watching from somewhere, snickering at us.

1184
01:00:49,680 --> 01:00:52,480
If so, I'm sure he'd appear before us

1185
01:00:52,480 --> 01:00:54,580
with that boastful look of his.

1186
01:00:54,580 --> 01:00:57,480
I'll go check from outside, so wait here.

1187
01:00:57,480 --> 01:00:59,390
Let me go with you!

1188
01:00:59,390 --> 01:01:02,590
It worries me to let you go alone.

1189
01:01:02,590 --> 01:01:04,190
Suit yourself.

1190
01:01:09,860 --> 01:01:12,370
Come on. He's still there.

1191
01:01:15,820 --> 01:01:18,320
He was smeared with blood, wasn't he?

1192
01:01:18,320 --> 01:01:20,120
Yeah. Let's hurry to the room.

1193
01:01:24,030 --> 01:01:25,430
You?

1194
01:01:32,640 --> 01:01:34,240
Shoots.

1195
01:01:36,040 --> 01:01:38,140
How is it, Heiji?

1196
01:01:39,610 --> 01:01:42,810
No good! He's really dead.

1197
01:01:49,120 --> 01:01:50,520
How are things?

1198
01:01:50,520 --> 01:01:51,620
Just as you can see,

1199
01:01:51,620 --> 01:01:53,920
he died on the spot after being hit on the head.

1200
01:01:53,920 --> 01:01:55,730
The murder weapon is probably that hammer.

1201
01:01:55,730 --> 01:01:57,630
It's got blood on it too.

1202
01:01:57,630 --> 01:01:59,730
It was probably taken from that toolbox

1203
01:01:59,730 --> 01:02:02,030
next to the lavender flowerpot.

1204
01:02:02,030 --> 01:02:03,230
Were the windows locked?

1205
01:02:03,230 --> 01:02:04,730
Yeah, they were,

1206
01:02:04,730 --> 01:02:08,640
nice and tight until I opened them.

1207
01:02:08,640 --> 01:02:12,110
The window frame also seems to be tightly in place with a screw.

1208
01:02:12,110 --> 01:02:16,710
The entrance door doesn't look to have been tampered with either.

1209
01:02:16,710 --> 01:02:20,720
Since there are no other escape holes or doors...

1210
01:02:20,820 --> 01:02:22,520
It's a locked room murder.

1211
01:02:22,520 --> 01:02:24,220
Moreover, the killers are either

1212
01:02:24,220 --> 01:02:25,620
Ms. Koshimizu,

1213
01:02:25,620 --> 01:02:28,830
Mr. Koya or Mr. Tsuchio, no?

1214
01:02:28,830 --> 01:02:30,530
What? Brat!

1215
01:02:30,530 --> 01:02:32,230
Why us?

1216
01:02:32,230 --> 01:02:33,630
True.

1217
01:02:33,630 --> 01:02:34,930
After Tokitsu left the room saying that

1218
01:02:34,930 --> 01:02:38,640
he was going to turn his room on the second floor into a locked room,

1219
01:02:38,640 --> 01:02:41,940
we began having dinner at the dining room downstairs.

1220
01:02:41,940 --> 01:02:45,910
I left to go to the restroom, and wasn't there for about ten minutes.

1221
01:02:46,110 --> 01:02:48,210
A few minutes after I returned,

1222
01:02:48,210 --> 01:02:51,210
Mr. Tsuchio went to his room to get his cigarettes

1223
01:02:51,210 --> 01:02:54,320
and Mr. Koya went to check on Tokitsu.

1224
01:02:54,320 --> 01:02:58,620
If all during that time, Hakuba and you two were together,

1225
01:02:58,620 --> 01:03:00,320
it would be most plausible.

1226
01:03:00,320 --> 01:03:03,830
Hold it, I was only hired to come here.

1227
01:03:03,830 --> 01:03:04,830
By who?

1228
01:03:04,830 --> 01:03:07,130
The TV station would never plan a program like this

1229
01:03:07,130 --> 01:03:09,030
where somebody would actually die, would they?

1230
01:03:09,030 --> 01:03:10,430
I really thought it was a program

1231
01:03:10,430 --> 01:03:11,940
that the TV station had planned to do.

1232
01:03:11,940 --> 01:03:14,340
I'm an actor and I belong to an acting school.

1233
01:03:14,340 --> 01:03:20,010
I received a letter asking to act the role of a TV director.

1234
01:03:20,010 --> 01:03:21,710
I was told I'd be given an advance payment of 500,000 yen,

1235
01:03:21,710 --> 01:03:23,110
and if the fact that I'm a fake is not revealed,

1236
01:03:23,110 --> 01:03:24,810
I was supposed to have received another 500,000 yen.

1237
01:03:24,810 --> 01:03:27,020
It's a great job that anybody would jump at, isn't it?

1238
01:03:27,020 --> 01:03:28,320
And, now that everything's out in the light?

1239
01:03:28,320 --> 01:03:33,520
Even so, if I just go through with the game,

1240
01:03:33,520 --> 01:03:36,330
I was told I'd be given half the pay, that's 250,000 yen.

1241
01:03:36,330 --> 01:03:40,230
Then, why did you go to your room to get your cigarette,

1242
01:03:40,230 --> 01:03:44,230
and yet go outside and get drenched in the rain?

1243
01:03:44,430 --> 01:03:46,340
I wanted to use the wireless radio that's in the shed

1244
01:03:46,340 --> 01:03:48,040
to make emergency contact.

1245
01:03:48,040 --> 01:03:49,040
But...

1246
01:03:49,040 --> 01:03:50,940
it was destroyed!

1247
01:03:50,940 --> 01:03:52,710
When I came to check the place out three days ago,

1248
01:03:52,710 --> 01:03:54,910
it was just fine.

1249
01:03:54,910 --> 01:03:56,710
-Honestly? -Yeah.

1250
01:03:56,710 --> 01:03:58,720
But, how strange.

1251
01:03:58,720 --> 01:04:02,620
You headed for the shed before this murder was committed.

1252
01:04:02,620 --> 01:04:06,320
How did you know that this sort of emergency was going to happen?

1253
01:04:06,320 --> 01:04:08,930
I just had a premonition.

1254
01:04:08,930 --> 01:04:11,230
Honestly.

1255
01:04:11,230 --> 01:04:15,630
Then, Mr. Koya, were also called by Mr. Tsuchio?

1256
01:04:15,630 --> 01:04:19,540
Yes, I came here two days ago to look after all of you.

1257
01:04:19,540 --> 01:04:22,340
I just happened to get time off

1258
01:04:22,340 --> 01:04:25,210
from the household that I serve as steward so.

1259
01:04:25,210 --> 01:04:28,210
But, you already knew the answer to the locked room murder, right?

1260
01:04:28,210 --> 01:04:30,410
Because you told us to write the answer down and take it to you.

1261
01:04:30,410 --> 01:04:33,320
I was told to say so if something happened in the locked room.

1262
01:04:33,320 --> 01:04:35,420
The order went on to say to sneak the answer sheet

1263
01:04:35,420 --> 01:04:37,920
under the toilet mat.

1264
01:04:37,920 --> 01:04:39,820
That's a clever way to put it.

1265
01:04:39,820 --> 01:04:42,430
As if there's someone else pulling the strings behind the scene.

1266
01:04:42,430 --> 01:04:44,330
No, I'm telling the truth.

1267
01:04:44,330 --> 01:04:47,730
Whatever the story, I'm in the same boat as you all are.

1268
01:04:47,730 --> 01:04:50,630
I was just told to come here as a high school detective

1269
01:04:50,630 --> 01:04:54,240
representing the south by that fake TV director.

1270
01:04:57,040 --> 01:04:58,610
I hate thunder!

1271
01:04:58,610 --> 01:05:01,110
So, please close the window, quick, please.

1272
01:05:01,110 --> 01:05:02,610
Yeah.

1273
01:05:03,710 --> 01:05:05,720
Don't worry. I'll silence the thunder

1274
01:05:05,720 --> 01:05:07,620
as well as the case soon.

1275
01:05:07,620 --> 01:05:09,520
What's with him?

1276
01:05:14,620 --> 01:05:17,430
At any rate, we three will check the place

1277
01:05:17,430 --> 01:05:19,930
so you three suspects wait in the first floor dining room

1278
01:05:19,930 --> 01:05:22,430
-till it's done. -If I could have my way,

1279
01:05:22,430 --> 01:05:26,140
I would like you to do likewise and wait with them too.

1280
01:05:26,140 --> 01:05:28,040
You're much too hot-tempered,

1281
01:05:28,040 --> 01:05:29,340
or should I say reckless?

1282
01:05:29,340 --> 01:05:30,940
What?

1283
01:05:30,940 --> 01:05:33,810
Look at the shattered pieces of glass!

1284
01:05:33,810 --> 01:05:37,110
And the footprints of your muddy shoes left on the desk!

