01:17:44,670 --> 01:17:46,870
seeing you counting them.

1538
01:17:48,380 --> 01:17:51,780
Well, you pretended to be afraid of the thunder and picked one up,

1539
01:17:51,780 --> 01:17:55,080
so I figured you had one on you.

1540
01:17:55,080 --> 01:17:57,690
You knew we were checking the shed.

1541
01:17:57,690 --> 01:17:59,290
You weren't afraid of thunder,

1542
01:17:59,290 --> 01:18:02,490
but rather, it's proof that you were watching outside.

1543
01:18:03,390 --> 01:18:05,060
You bent down then to pick up the screw

1544
01:18:05,060 --> 01:18:08,260
that you failed to pick up previously, right?

1545
01:18:11,570 --> 01:18:12,770
Am I wrong?

1546
01:18:12,770 --> 01:18:15,170
Oh, that's probably...

1547
01:18:17,470 --> 01:18:20,480
To hide the hole for your pierced ear.

1548
01:18:20,480 --> 01:18:22,580
You covered your ears to hide it, right?

1549
01:18:22,580 --> 01:18:24,180
Huh, pierce...

1550
01:18:24,180 --> 01:18:25,580
But...

1551
01:18:25,580 --> 01:18:28,180
That's why you were wearing a headphone on the ship, right?

1552
01:18:28,180 --> 01:18:29,580
Because if your hair blew in the sea breeze,

1553
01:18:29,580 --> 01:18:31,190
it would reveal your pierced ears.

1554
01:18:31,190 --> 01:18:34,990
Well, there are a lot of students with pierced ears in England,

1555
01:18:34,990 --> 01:18:36,890
so I didn't even bother to notice.

1556
01:18:36,890 --> 01:18:39,360
But, I thought your high school was really strict

1557
01:18:39,360 --> 01:18:42,260
that you could never be allowed pierced ears.

1558
01:18:42,260 --> 01:18:44,470
Yes, but it's okay already.

1559
01:18:44,470 --> 01:18:46,070
I'm already 20,

1560
01:18:46,070 --> 01:18:48,870
and I've graduated high school two years ago.

1561
01:18:48,870 --> 01:18:52,870
I took my old uniform out to hide what I could,

1562
01:18:53,070 --> 01:18:54,580
but goofed.

1563
01:18:54,580 --> 01:18:56,480
I even went as far as to talk about school rules

1564
01:18:56,480 --> 01:18:58,980
so that I would look like a high school girl.

1565
01:18:58,980 --> 01:19:02,580
But, why did you gather us high school detectives

1566
01:19:02,580 --> 01:19:04,790
and do something like this?

1567
01:19:06,790 --> 01:19:10,090
I wanted to find out about something.

1568
01:19:10,090 --> 01:19:11,660
And, what's that?

1569
01:19:11,660 --> 01:19:15,360
The homicide at Lavender Manor.

1570
01:19:15,360 --> 01:19:17,870
You wanted to know who the high school detective that solved it was, right?

1571
01:19:17,870 --> 01:19:19,170
Yes.

1572
01:19:19,170 --> 01:19:23,670
Then, you mean it was... Tokitsu?

1573
01:19:23,670 --> 01:19:28,180
Although the name and details of the case wasn't written in the papers.

1574
01:19:28,180 --> 01:19:31,480
Yes, he happened to drop by at the mansion

1575
01:19:31,480 --> 01:19:33,580
while traveling through Shikoku,

1576
01:19:33,580 --> 01:19:37,890
solved the locked room case and left without saying his name.

1577
01:19:37,890 --> 01:19:38,990
Because of him,

1578
01:19:38,990 --> 01:19:42,890
my best friend who was working as a housekeeper there was suspected.

1579
01:19:42,890 --> 01:19:43,990
She was suspected on the grounds

1580
01:19:43,990 --> 01:19:48,260
that she was with the lady of the house, just two of them together.

1581
01:19:48,260 --> 01:19:52,870
I also went to that mansion as a detective,

1582
01:19:52,870 --> 01:19:55,770
a month before that man appeared.

1583
01:19:55,770 --> 01:19:58,770
My best friend asked me to investigate the case

1584
01:19:58,770 --> 01:20:01,080
because it could be a homicide.

1585
01:20:07,780 --> 01:20:11,290
But, I couldn't come up with anything.

1586
01:20:11,290 --> 01:20:13,790
I couldn't think of anything other than the fact that

1587
01:20:13,790 --> 01:20:17,560
she had locked herself in her room and committed suicide.

1588
01:20:17,560 --> 01:20:21,960
Then, why was your best friend suspected?

1589
01:20:21,960 --> 01:20:25,570
The high school detective that came two months later

1590
01:20:25,570 --> 01:20:28,470
found outside the window of her room

1591
01:20:28,470 --> 01:20:30,770
scattered screws with heads cut off

1592
01:20:30,770 --> 01:20:36,480
as well as the fact that the window was only pasted on with glue.

1593
01:20:36,480 --> 01:20:38,780
You mean you overlooked it?

1594
01:20:38,780 --> 01:20:40,580
Overlooked it my foot.

1595
01:20:40,580 --> 01:20:42,180
The man called Tsuchio

1596
01:20:42,180 --> 01:20:44,390
disguised himself as a cleaning staff

1597
01:20:44,390 --> 01:20:46,690
and set up the trick.

1598
01:20:46,690 --> 01:20:50,290
He probably rigged the window so that it would come off easily,

1599
01:20:50,290 --> 01:20:53,760
when he planned to come back to rob the house later.

1600
01:20:53,760 --> 01:20:56,960
That's why when you heard of the Lavender Manor,

1601
01:20:56,960 --> 01:21:00,970
you went pale and wanted to escape from the island.

1602
01:21:01,170 --> 01:21:03,070
Six months after the incident,

1603
01:21:03,070 --> 01:21:05,370
Tokitsu jumps onto the trick,

1604
01:21:05,370 --> 01:21:07,480
as if to boast his power of deduction,

1605
01:21:07,480 --> 01:21:11,080
reports to the police and the media that this is a homicide.

1606
01:21:11,080 --> 01:21:12,380
"New Truth Disclosed on Suicide of the Lady of Lavender Manor"

1607
01:21:12,380 --> 01:21:13,880
"Police Conclude it to be Locked Room Homicide!"

1608
01:21:13,880 --> 01:21:15,280
"Suspect Still Denies Charges"

1609
01:21:15,280 --> 01:21:18,190
If the rust of the screws were checked,

1610
01:21:18,190 --> 01:21:19,390
it would've been obvious whether it had anything

1611
01:21:19,390 --> 01:21:21,390
to do with the case or not.

1612
01:21:21,390 --> 01:21:24,090
Tokitsu, realized that something was not right,

1613
01:21:24,090 --> 01:21:26,460
so he didn't disclose his name.

1614
01:21:26,460 --> 01:21:30,770
That's why I couldn't tell which high school detective it was.

1615
01:21:30,770 --> 01:21:32,470
The only clue I had

1616
01:21:32,470 --> 01:21:36,470
was the message that my best friend left me before she died.

1617
01:21:36,470 --> 01:21:38,670
A high school detective that speaks with a strange accent

1618
01:21:38,670 --> 01:21:40,370
suspects me.

1619
01:21:40,370 --> 01:21:43,080
Help me. Help me, Natsuki!

1620
01:21:43,080 --> 01:21:45,080
That's all she left behind.

1621
01:21:53,990 --> 01:21:55,190
I see.

1622
01:21:55,190 --> 01:21:57,190
"A strange accent"

1623
01:21:57,190 --> 01:21:59,460
Since I've been living abroad for a while,

1624
01:21:59,460 --> 01:22:01,960
sometimes my Japanese is funny.

1625
01:22:01,960 --> 01:22:04,170
Hattori speaks with a super Kansai accent,

1626
01:22:04,170 --> 01:22:06,370
and Tokitsu talks in old Japanese.

1627
01:22:06,370 --> 01:22:08,670
That's why you gathered us all here.

1628
01:22:08,670 --> 01:22:10,370
Yes, moreover,

1629
01:22:10,370 --> 01:22:15,280
only you three had strong connections with the police too.

1630
01:22:15,280 --> 01:22:19,680
Which means that Kudo wasn't included to begin with?

1631
01:22:19,680 --> 01:22:20,780
Okay.

1632
01:22:20,780 --> 01:22:24,190
Yes, I just used his name to call Hakuba over

1633
01:22:24,190 --> 01:22:26,690
because Kudo is famous.

1634
01:22:26,690 --> 01:22:29,790
And, at this lodge where you gathered all the detectives,

1635
01:22:29,790 --> 01:22:32,360
you first put Mr. Tsuchio to sleep and tied him up,

1636
01:22:32,360 --> 01:22:36,360
created a locked room just like the one at Lavender Manor

1637
01:22:36,560 --> 01:22:39,170
and got hold of the target you were after.

1638
01:22:39,170 --> 01:22:43,170
Yes, if I put the necessary tools in the room

1639
01:22:43,270 --> 01:22:45,970
filled with the fragrance of lavender,

1640
01:22:45,970 --> 01:22:49,880
the high school detective would recall the case immediately

1641
01:22:49,880 --> 01:22:52,380
and see through the trick.

1642
01:22:52,380 --> 01:22:57,590
That mansion was really virtually buried in lavender.

1643
01:22:57,590 --> 01:22:58,890
Isn't that right,

1644
01:22:58,890 --> 01:23:02,290
Mr. Renzo Koya who used to work as the steward of that mansion?

1645
01:23:06,960 --> 01:23:11,670
Yes, because the lady of the house loved them very much.

1646
01:23:14,770 --> 01:23:16,970
Miss!

1647
01:23:20,370 --> 01:23:22,780
Then, why did you call him here?

1648
01:23:22,780 --> 01:23:25,280
He knew why the lady of the house committed suicide

1649
01:23:25,280 --> 01:23:26,480
and yet he didn't say a word about it.

1650
01:23:26,480 --> 01:23:28,580
That's because...

1651
01:23:28,580 --> 01:23:30,890
Miss, please don't take anymore medicine!

1652
01:23:30,890 --> 01:23:34,790
Quiet, let me do as I please!

1653
01:23:34,790 --> 01:23:37,860
I couldn't say a word

1654
01:23:37,860 --> 01:23:40,860
to protect the honor of the lady of the house.

1655
01:23:40,860 --> 01:23:42,660
I thought that suspicion against her

1656
01:23:42,660 --> 01:23:44,970
would clear as investigations progressed.

1657
01:23:44,970 --> 01:23:45,970
"Suspect of Locked Room Murder Commits Suicide"

1658
01:23:45,970 --> 01:23:48,870
I never imagined something like that would happen.

1659
01:23:48,870 --> 01:23:52,070
Please accept my apologies.

1660
01:23:52,070 --> 01:23:54,380
But... hold it.

1661
01:23:54,380 --> 01:23:57,580
If you called these two here that you have a grudge against...

1662
01:23:57,580 --> 01:24:00,780
Right, nobody will come for you.

1663
01:24:00,780 --> 01:24:02,480
Back then, I told the captain of the ship that

1664
01:24:02,480 --> 01:24:03,880
if he can't keep a secret,

1665
01:24:03,880 --> 01:24:05,290
I'm not going to pay him the remainder,

1666
01:24:05,290 --> 01:24:07,690
to make sure he wouldn't talk.

1667
01:24:07,690 --> 01:24:10,390
I couldn't afford having him run away on me,

1668
01:24:10,390 --> 01:24:12,960
even if he were to realize what my plan was.

1669
01:24:12,960 --> 01:24:15,260
I had that in mind too.

1670
01:24:15,260 --> 01:24:19,170
As for Tokitsu, he kept explaining his mistaken deduction

1671
01:24:19,170 --> 01:24:23,570
of the murder at Lavender Manor up to the time he was killed by me.

1672
01:24:23,570 --> 01:24:25,770
He was really someone not worth bothering with.

1673
01:24:25,770 --> 01:24:28,380
So, you're the one who broke the wireless radio too.

1674
01:24:28,380 --> 01:24:30,680
Of course I'm the one who broke it.

1675
01:24:30,680 --> 01:24:33,080
We all die together.

1676
01:24:35,180 --> 01:24:37,590
I'm sorry, sonny.

1677
01:24:37,590 --> 01:24:39,890
No need to apologize!

1678
01:24:39,890 --> 01:24:43,690
They'll come to save us, I know!

1679
01:24:45,260 --> 01:24:50,360
You said that you came here a half day earlier than us, right?

1680
01:24:50,360 --> 01:24:53,070
Didn't you come here with your own cruiser?

1681
01:24:53,070 --> 01:24:54,670
No, I just happened to arrive

1682
01:24:54,670 --> 01:24:57,670
earlier than scheduled at the harbor.

1683
01:24:57,670 --> 01:24:59,870
I heard that it was a lodge that was not in use for a while

1684
01:24:59,870 --> 01:25:02,780
and that I was going to be sleeping together with many people so...

1685
01:25:02,780 --> 01:25:06,480
I looked for a ship that recently shipped daily necessities and food

1686
01:25:06,480 --> 01:25:07,780
to an uninhabited island,

1687
01:25:07,780 --> 01:25:09,980
and had them bring me here,

1688
01:25:09,980 --> 01:25:12,190
after paying a hefty sum of money.

1689
01:25:12,190 --> 01:25:16,190
Which means that nobody knows you're here?

1690
01:25:16,290 --> 01:25:19,760
No, and how about you, haven't you told anybody?

1691
01:25:19,760 --> 01:25:22,060
Well, I sort of did, but...

1692
01:25:22,060 --> 01:25:24,270
She's kind of dense.

1693
01:25:24,270 --> 01:25:25,970
What?

1694
01:25:28,970 --> 01:25:29,970
A sound?

1695
01:25:29,970 --> 01:25:32,170
What's this sound?

1696
01:25:33,370 --> 01:25:36,080
Don't tell me that the generator also broke down.

1697
01:25:36,080 --> 01:25:38,480
It's not the sound of the generator!

1698
01:25:38,480 --> 01:25:40,380
Then, what's this sound?

1699
01:25:43,380 --> 01:25:47,890
Heiji!

1700
01:25:49,490 --> 01:25:51,060
It's Kazuha!

1701
01:25:51,060 --> 01:25:53,460
Kazuha brought a ship along!

1702
01:25:53,460 --> 01:25:54,660
Why?

1703
01:25:54,660 --> 01:25:59,370
Heiji left a message and landmark behind.

1704
01:25:59,370 --> 01:26:04,270
Yeah, I leave a message saying "Heiji Hattori was here!"

1705
01:26:11,880 --> 01:26:14,780
Oh, there he is! It's Heiji and Conan too!

1706
01:26:14,780 --> 01:26:17,690
Really, it's Heiji!

1707
01:26:17,690 --> 01:26:20,590
God, if you spit it out right away,

1708
01:26:20,590 --> 01:26:23,790
you wouldn't have had to take on five throws over the shoulder.

1709
01:26:23,790 --> 01:26:25,260
It was six.

1710
01:26:25,260 --> 01:26:26,760
What?

1711
01:26:29,260 --> 01:26:34,070
I'm glad there are hot-blooded detectives like you around.

1712
01:26:34,070 --> 01:26:36,870
I smear the door knob with blood and you break the door down,

1713
01:26:36,870 --> 01:26:39,170
then you crack the glass window and break in.

1714
01:26:39,170 --> 01:26:43,180
Thanks to you, the dead body ends up leaning against the window.

1715
01:26:43,280 --> 01:26:45,780
If you charge forward body and all and the entire window falls off,

1716
01:26:45,780 --> 01:26:47,180
that's it.

1717
01:26:47,180 --> 01:26:50,380
Sorry, that I'm so hot tempered and rash.

1718
01:26:50,380 --> 01:26:53,990
Nope, to believe that a person is alive

1719
01:26:53,990 --> 01:26:56,390
till you confirm the person's death

1720
01:26:56,390 --> 01:26:59,360
is what a famed detective is all about.

1721
01:26:59,360 --> 01:27:01,060
Right, sonny?

1722
01:27:06,470 --> 01:27:09,170
If god would allow me to...

1723
01:27:09,170 --> 01:27:13,170
I would really have liked to have a Detective Championship

1724
01:27:13,370 --> 01:27:15,280
with both of you.

1725
01:27:18,080 --> 01:27:22,080
If I could only go back to my high school days without worry.

1726
01:28:48,570 --> 01:28:51,870
And? Is Kudo there?

1727
01:28:53,270 --> 01:28:55,180
I'm not sure.

1728
01:28:57,080 --> 01:28:59,680
Of course he's not.

1729
01:29:01,280 --> 01:29:03,600
Next Conan's Hint:

1730
01:29:03,920 --> 01:29:05,900
Local newspaper.

1731
01:29:06,160 --> 01:29:08,640
-Haibara, where is your home town? -Doc's place.

1732
01:29:08,640 --> 01:29:10,420
-No way. -Indeed.

1733
01:29:10,460 --> 01:29:11,460
Yeah.

